## Interpretation

The native app prerequisite surface is aligned:

- The installed app contains TriggerPoller and handleAgentTrigger code paths.
- The app process is running.
- The app default device id matches Theo and Maya.
- Theo and Maya are active_graph agents on the Codex provider/model/harness/local
  execution path.
- The stale Theo/Maya trigger queue was clear at audit time.
- The bridge is running as mitigation.

The remaining native blocker is therefore not explained by harness mismatch,
wrong device id for Theo/Maya, missing binary trigger code, stale queue backlog,
or bridge attribution confusion. Native Pentagon handoff activation remains red
because the app still does not claim a fresh valid target trigger during the
bounded native-only probe window.

